      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That's an interesting take. When you say \"stability,\" are you implying that these demographic shifts naturally create friction with the existing system? Like, even if people assimilate, some analysts argue that the sheer scale of the change in voting blocs or cultural makeup could fundamentally destabilize the traditional way things are run. Do you see that as a real risk?",
